<div id="review_1675308615" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1675308615" />
    <a title="Leslie Noble" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/23503654-leslie-noble"><img alt="Leslie Noble" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1442944929p2/23503654.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1675308615?book_show_action=true">Mar 27, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Leslie Noble" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Leslie Noble" href="/user/show/23503654-leslie-noble">Leslie Noble</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1675308615" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8403101390868744109">A brilliant sequel and tribute to the Erskine Childers classic book The Riddle of the Sands. It takes and develops the characters of that book, the historic and geographic settings, and the situation, with seamless skill to produce a fascinating and exciting read. Sam Llewellyn has the same talents as Erskine Childers for vivid descriptions in the sailing scenes, to satisfy the most critical yachting enthusiast.<br/>The two books are best read back-to-back, even if &apos;Riddle&apos; has been read previously. </span>
  <span id="freeText8403101390868744109" style="display:none">A brilliant sequel and tribute to the Erskine Childers classic book The Riddle of the Sands. It takes and develops the characters of that book, the historic and geographic settings, and the situation, with seamless skill to produce a fascinating and exciting read. Sam Llewellyn has the same talents as Erskine Childers for vivid descriptions in the sailing scenes, to satisfy the most critical yachting enthusiast.<br />The two books are best read back-to-back, even if 'Riddle' has been read previously. Re-reading that before launching into 'Shadow' gives the proper background for the follow-up tale, and adds to the enjoyment.</span>
  <a data-text-id="8403101390868744109" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


